To those of you who might be stuck at 99.8 percent -- you have the full mpg file, just not the two gratuitous jpg images which have nothing to do with the actual video anyway.

Also, if you have the original file that didn't come from this torrent and run Video Inspector (or other video verify utility) you will find that it says the file is not complete. Technically true. It will still play completely through without a hiccup or any other sign that it's incomplete. When you make a torrent -- the torrent maker app "knows" it's not a complete file (even though it is for all intents and purposes) and this torrent will forever sit at 99.8 percent. The original mpeg file is corrupt -- not the torrent. Although the inoperable jpg files make that last statement questionable.

Lastly, I would like to advise the uploader (monnet) that it's not a good idea to upload 9 torrents at a time if you don't have a high speed internet connection. Of all the facial abuse torrents, I know that two were completed quickly due to outside help (myself, for one). The rest (not counting Insomnia and Hazel) are crawling along at dial-up speed, or aren't being seeded at all. Upload one at a time and everyone will be much happier. :)
